   "narrative": "Daniel J. Gallivan of Holyoke enlisted in 1898, the year of the Spanish-American War, and made the Army his life. He served with Company E, 14th Infantry, on the Mexican Border and in the Panama Canal Zone, and he rose to the rank of Sergeant — the rank that runs an army from the inside, where a company's discipline, its rations, and the training of its young men all rest. He died of heart disease at Fort George Wright, Washington, on February 21, 1918, after twenty years in uniform, in the first year of the war he had spent his career preparing for. If you have further information about this veteran, please contact the City of Holyoke Veterans Graves Officer at (413) 322-5630 at 310 Appleton Street, 1st Floor, Holyoke, MA 01040.",
