   "narrative": "Roland A. Hamelin of Holyoke died in his country's service on July 1, 1944, in July 1944, as the American armies fought through the Normandy hedgerows and the Marines took Saipan and Guam. Wounds, disease, and accident took American servicemen as surely as enemy fire — in training camps, aboard transports, in aircraft that never reached the enemy, and in hospitals far from any battlefield. His unit and his resting place have not yet been established. If you have further information about this veteran, please contact the City of Holyoke Veterans Graves Officer at (413) 322-5630 at 310 Appleton Street, 1st Floor, Holyoke, MA 01040.",
