   "extraPhotos": [],
   "narrative": "Edwin R. Kingsland, a son of Holyoke, entered the service in April 1917, attending Plattsburg Camp, and was assigned to the Massachusetts Institute of Technology for aviation training. He was transferred to Canada, where he flew with the British Royal Flying Corps, and then to Camp Hicks, Texas, where he received his First Lieutenant's commission. He went overseas in February 1918, attached to the 8th Aero Squadron. He was killed in a flying accident in France on August 1, 1918. In the first years of military aviation a pilot's life at the front was measured in weeks, and as many airmen died in training and accidents as ever fell to an enemy gun. If you have further information about this veteran, please contact the City of Holyoke Veterans Graves Officer at (413) 322-5630 at 310 Appleton Street, 1st Floor, Holyoke, MA 01040.",
