   "narrative": "Michael J. Moriarty of Holyoke entered the service in 1915 and served with Company D, 2nd Massachusetts Regiment at the Mexican Border in 1916. He was transferred to the First Vermont Infantry at Camp Bartlett, and then to Camp Greene, North Carolina, where his regiment was rebuilt as a pioneer infantry unit. The pioneers were soldiers who fought as infantry and worked as laborers — digging trenches, cutting roads, and hauling supplies forward under shellfire so the front-line divisions could advance. He served as a Sergeant with Company D, 60th Pioneer Infantry, and died of disease in France on October 12, 1918. If you have further information about this veteran, please contact the City of Holyoke Veterans Graves Officer at (413) 322-5630 at 310 Appleton Street, 1st Floor, Holyoke, MA 01040.",
