   "narrative": "George F. Varney of Holyoke entered the service in September 1917 with the Supply Company, 1st Infantry, and was stationed at Camp Kearny, California. He died there on November 7, 1918, of pneumonia — four days before the Armistice. If you have further information about this veteran, please contact the City of Holyoke Veterans Graves Officer at (413) 322-5630 at 310 Appleton Street, 1st Floor, Holyoke, MA 01040.",
