   "era": "World War II",
   "branch": "Navy",
   "branchLabel": "U.S. Navy – World War II",
   "lat": null,
   "lng": null,
   "photo": "",
   "extraPhotos": [],
   "narrative": "Bolek Stanley Warzenski of Holyoke served as a Soundman Third Class in the United States Naval Reserve. The soundmen worked the sonar — sitting in a darkened compartment with headphones, listening into the water for the echo of a submarine, and calling the attack when they found one. In the Battle of the Atlantic, a convoy's survival could turn on what one soundman heard. He died in his country's service. He was survived by his wife, Mrs. Dorothy Rose Warzenski. If you have further information about this veteran, please contact the City of Holyoke Veterans Graves Officer at (413) 322-5630 at 310 Appleton Street, 1st Floor, Holyoke, MA 01040.",
